	</div>
</div>
<div class="row">
	<div class="span6">	
		<h3>3 Most Important Tasks</h3>
		<p>What are the three most important things you should do today?  I know you have a lot to do, but really trim this down to three, one is even better.</p>
		<p>Start with "I would consider today a success if I..." what?  That's the thing you need to add to MIT.</p>
		<p>I like to set up 3 MIT's for my week (weekly planning grid coming soon), and then I use those and other info to help me decide what are my MIT today!</p>
	</div>	
</div>

<div class="row">
	<div class="span6">	
		<h3>Action Items</h3>
		<p>The next time one of your coworkers walks up and asks you to do something, quickly capture it as an action item and get back to work!</p>
	</div>	
</div>

<div class="row">
	<div class="span6">
		<h3>Notes</h3>
		<p>I see, it's not your coworkers, it's your own mind.  It's always coming up with ideas isn't it? Quickly jot those ideas down in the note sections and get back to work!</p>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="row">
	<div class="span6">
		<h3>Activity Log</h3>
		<p>The only way to know if you're actually GTD is to track your progress.  That's what the activity log is for.  Over the years I've created a short hand method for quickly capturing what I'm working on.</p>		
	</div>
</div>

<div class="row">
	<div class="span3">
		<h4>Productive p</h4>
		<p>For example, let's say I spent 30 minutes responding to email about an important project. My log entry would look something like this:</p>		
		<p><code>p 800-830, responded to email re:big huge project. created discussion on base camp</code></p>
		<p>let me break that down:
			<ul>
				<li>p = productive</li>
				<li>800-830 = 8:00am to 8:30am </li>
				<li>, = anything after the comma is a brief description of what I did</li>
			</ul>
		</p>
	</div>
	<div class="span3">
		<h4>Externally Distraction [e]</h4>
		<p>We are interrupted all the time.  When these interruptions last more than 10 minutes I like to log them so that I can see if there are any patterns</p>
		<p><code>[e] 800-830, chatted with team mates about the iOS meetup</code></p>
		<p>let me break that down:
			<ul>
				<li>[e] = external distraction</li>
				<li>800-830 = 8:00am to 8:30am </li>
				<li>, = anything after the comma is a brief description of what I did</li>
			</ul>
		</p>
	</div>
	<div class="span3">
		<h4>Internally Distraction [i]</h4>
		<p>We all accidentally click a link from our twitter feed and end up surfing the web mindlessly from time to time.  If this happens for more than 10 minutes I log it too</p>
		<p><code>[i] 800-830, got lost on lifehacker trying to be productive...:O</code></p>
		<p>let me break that down:
			<ul>
				<li>[i] = internal distraction</li>
				<li>800-830 = 8:00am to 8:30am </li>
				<li>, = anything after the comma is a brief description of what I did</li>
			</ul>
		</p>
	</div>
	<div class="span3">
		<h4>Pomodoro (p)</h4>
		<p>I use the pomodoro technique when I really want to focus on a distinct task for a block of time.  It's an awesome technique for getting things done!</p>
		<p><code>(p) 800-830, completed edit workflow in the activity list</code></p>
		<p>let me break that down:
			<ul>
				<li>(p) = pomodoro - complete focus on task at hand</li>
				<li>800-830 = 8:00am to 8:30am </li>
				<li>, = anything after the comma is a brief description of what I did</li>
			</ul>
		</p>		
	</div>
</div>
	
	
